tty --> teletypes

  /dev/ttySn --> serial port terminal
  /dev/tty --> controlling terminal
  /dev/ttyn, /dev/console --> console

  pty --> peseudo terminal, /dev/pty/mn /dev/pty/sn
  pts/ptmx  --> pty


  

If you use Alpha/DualOS QLD platform:
    When you make menuconfig and select Comms Enable:
        Tick Use QCOM Protocol Qpv1.6.3
        Tick Dont use Microblaze serial port for COMMS
        Untick everything else

    Goto game_proc/egm/comms
        Modify base/comms.c, add following code into Comms Constructor:
       
         if (grantpt(fd) == -1 || unlockpt(fd) == -1)
        {
            cerr << strerror(errno) << endl;
        }
        else
        {
            const char* slave = ptsname(fd);
            if (!slave)
            {
                std::cout<< "unable to retrive slave device name" << endl;
            }
            else
            {
                std::cout << ">>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>" << endl <<
                             slave << endl <<
                             "<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<" << endl;
            }
        }

        Modify qcom/qfunctions.c, change line 39:
            c = new CommsQcom("/dev/ptmx")

        Modify qcom/qcom_lib.c line 3077:
            #ifndef __COMMS_QCOM_USE_SERIAL__
                qcom_ptr->comms_enabled = 1;
            #endif
 
If you use P4 platform, then you have no need to do the last change.

usage:
run game as normal
check the game output to find the slave device opened by game, such as /dev/pts/15
run simulation with -d option: ./simulator -d /dev/pts/15
enter command: seek [To find available EGM]
enter command: ls [To check the EGMs found by seek]
enter command: pa [To config EGM poll address]
enter command: configrequest --mef --gcr --psn [To send EGM config request]
enter command: egmconfig --jur 1 --den 1 --tok 100 [To config EGM with marke QLD; denomination 1c; token value 100]
enter command: gameconfig --var 89 --gameenable [To enable game with variation 89]
or
enter command: gameconfig --var 90 --gameenable --pgid 1234 --jptype 1 1 --amount 1000000 500000 [To config game with 2 level lp which intial amount are 1000000 and 50000]
enter command: gm --gvn [GVN] --var 90 --mef --gef --gamecfg [To verify the game configuration]

Polling Cycle and Responose

Start Poll Cycle
SC --> Poll --> EGM A
SC <-- Response <-- EGM A
SC --> Poll --> EGM B
SC <-- Response <-- EGM B
... ...
SC --> Broadcast Messages --> All EGM
End Poll Cycle

--> EGM Configuration Request Poll
<-- EGM Configuratioon Response

--> EGM Configuration Poll
<-- Game Configuration Response for GVN 1
<-- Game Configuration Response for GVN 2
... ...
<-- Game Configuration Response for GVN N

--> Game Configuration Poll for GVN 1
<-- Game Configuration Response for GVN 1

